author: Nexcell Pride
text:
Intense streaming today... :_ちょうちょ:

Rushia maybe lost the practicing at this game, but she still doing her best. :_ちょうちょ:
About the comments about "bullying her at game" noticed at LiveChat... Well, maybe she would have a fun moments from herself than from other players, I can't explain it well.
Anyway, she became more closer today at inviting all players. :_るんるん:

And maybe everyone couldn't notice about her contagious maniac laughter, which possibly needs a clipping about her laughters than her raging and/or crying moments. :_きゅん:

Oh... The crown she used... I remember the "Minecraft at Tanabata" and the "Toyboxing" streams... 👑

And the Supaachaato Orei Time... I don't know if someone have noticed about CGI, but the "Supaachaato Orei Time" logo is back later of at least 2 months without using it. I though that following scrolling message is replacing the logos (The message says: "Reading and Thanking Supaachaato. Today's Stream is Ended")
As curiosity: "Supaachaato Orei Time" logo debuted about March or April 2020, and used regularly until August 2020 (First "Fall Guys" stream) when the Scrolling message and "Supacha Yomi Time" logo debuted and used until October 2020 ("51 games - Toyboxing" stream) when due to an extra gameplay, "Supacha Yomi Time" logo disappeared.
"Supaachaato Orei Time" logo also was used at ASMR streams (Only the 2nd August ASMR and the September one)

And Superchats goes Vrooomm when Rushia went to another site and later returned...

Obviously Rushia-daitenshi is more lovely yet... Her chuu's are more recurrent than before September. :_ハート:
(I remember the first "chuu" at her 3D premiere)

As conclusion... She deserves all world's love. :_きゅん: :_ちょうちょ:
